OL,3,CCommons Speaker Sir Lindsay Hoyle
OL,4,Cunder pressure - what happens next?
OL,6,FThe Speaker of the House of Commons
OL,7,Fchairs debates that happen in the
OL,8,FHouse of Commons chamber.
OL,10,FThey control the debate, decide who
OL,11,Fcan speak and chooses which amendments
OL,12,Fare debated and voted on.
OL,14,FThe Speaker is an MP who has been
OL,15,Felected to the position by other MPs.
OL,17,FSir Lindsay , having been a Labour MP
OL,18,Ffor Chorley since 1997 and having
OL,19,Fserved as Deputy Speaker to John
OL,20,FBercow for nine years.
