OL,3,CCommons Speaker Sir Lindsay Hoyle
OL,4,Cunder pressure - what happens next?
OL,6,FA new Speaker is elected by secret
OL,7,Fballot and they must also be re-
OL,8,Felected after each general election.
OL,10,FIf a candidate receives more than 50%
OL,11,Fof the votes, their election to the
OL,12,Frole as Speaker is put to the House as
OL,13,Fa question.
OL,15,FIf no candidate received more than
OL,16,Fhalf of the votes, the candidate with
OL,17,Fthe fewest votes is eliminated, along
OL,18,Fwith anybody who received fewer than
OL,19,F5% of the votes, and MPs vote again.
